        <h1>LeetCode 696: Count Binary Substrings (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given a binary string s, return the number of non-empty substrings that have the same number of 0's and
                1's, and all the 0's and all the 1's in these substrings are grouped consecutively. Substrings that
                occur multiple times are counted the number of times they occur.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: s = "00110011"<br>
                Output: 6<br>
                Explanation: There are 6 substrings with equal consecutive 0's and 1's: "0011", "01", "1100", "10",
                "0011", and "01". Note that some substrings repeat and are counted multiple times.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int countBinarySubstrings(string s) {
        int n = s.size();
        int answer = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i &lt; n - 1; i++) {
            if(s[i] != s[i + 1]) {  
                int left = i;
                int right = i + 1;
                // Expand while balanced 0s and 1s
                while(left &gt;= 0 &amp;&amp; right &lt; n &amp;&amp; s[left] == s[i] &amp;&amp; s[right] == s[i + 1]) {
                    answer++;
                    left--;
                    right++;
                }
            }
        }
        return answer;
    }
};</code></pre>
